ldItem -Path 'C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw' -Recurse -Filter '*.json' | Select-String -Pattern 'openclaw agent --agent' -SimpleMatch | Select-Object -First 10\",\"yieldMs\":10000,\"timeout\":30}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","usage":{"input":352,"output":142,"cacheRead":15872,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16366,"cost":{"input":0.000264,"output":0.000639,"cacheRead":0.0011903999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0020934}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775251334453,"responseId":"resp_046f5ebea25545fb0169d02f8756ec8191a4273e8dd3d952c0"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6d599ed2","parentId":"5cf04df7","timestamp":"2026-04-03T21:22:21.013Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ZzU6GFTtO50FupgnS2din9sP|fc_046f5ebea25545fb0169d02f8b9f1c8191b37dae8582a12148","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\subagents\\runs.json:1139:      \"frozenResultText\": \"Here are the findings:\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \r\nResearch Findings: OpenClaw Agent Runtime Invocation\\n\\n### (1) Current CLI command to run an agent directly\\n\\n**Yes \r\n- `openclaw agent` exists today and is fully functional.**\\n\\n```bash\\n# Send a message to the main agent (via \r\nGateway)\\nopenclaw agent --agent main --message \\\"do something\\\"\\n\\n# Run embedded locally (requires API keys in shell \r\nenv - no Gateway needed)\\nopenclaw agent --agent main --message \\\"do something\\\" --local\\n\\n# Target a specific \r\nsession\\nopenclaw agent --session-id <id> --message \\\"text\\\"\\n\\n# Deliver reply back to a channel\\nopenclaw agent \r\n--agent ops --message \\\"Generate report\\\" --deliver --reply-channel slack --reply-to \\\"#reports\\\"\\n```\\n\\nSource: \r\n`docs/cli/agent.md` and `openclaw agent --help`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### (2) Two runtime paths exist\\n\\n| Mode | How | When \r\n|\\n|---|---|---|\\n| **Gateway-backed** (default) | Forwards to the running Gateway over WebSocket | Gateway must be \r\nrunning; normal operation |\\n| **Embedded/local** (`--local`) | Runs agent in-process directly | Requires provider API \r\nkeys in shell env; no Gateway needed |\\n\\n---\\n\\n### (3) Sessions/subagents/APIs are the standard bridge\\n\\nYes. The \r\nintended pattern for spawning isolated agent turns programmatically is:\\n\\n- **`openclaw agent`** - CLI one-shot \r\nturn\\n- **`openclaw acp`** - ACP protocol bridge over stdio for IDE integrations (forwards to Gateway via \r\nWebSocket)\\n- **Sessions** (`openclaw sessions`) - manage stored conversation state; not themselves an execution \r\nsurface\\n- **Cron jobs** (`openclaw cron`) - scheduled recurring agent turns\\n- **Hooks** - event-triggered agent \r\nturns\\n\\nThe ACP bridge (`openclaw acp`) is the intended path for programmatic IDE/code-level integration, and it \r\nroutes through the Gateway session system.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### (4) Concrete supported patterns today\\n\\n```bash\\n# One-shot \r\nagent turn (Gateway mode)\\nopenclaw agent --agent main --message \\\"Summarize logs\\\"\\n\\n# One-shot agent turn \r\n(embedded, no Gateway needed)\\nopenclaw agent --agent main --message \\\"Summarize logs\\\" --local\\n\\n# ACP bridge (for \r\nIDE integrations - speaks ACP over stdio, forwards to Gateway)\\nopenclaw acp\\nopenclaw acp --session \r\nagent:main:main\\nopenclaw acp --url wss://gateway-host:18789 --token <token>\\n\\n# Scheduled agent turn via \r\ncron\\nopenclaw cron add --job \\\"daily-report\\\" --schedule \\\"0 9 * * *\\\" --agent main --message \\\"Generate daily \r\nreport\\\"\\n\\n# Send message to channel (not agent turn, but triggers agent via channel routing)\\nopenclaw message send \r\n--channel telegram --target @user --message \\\"...\\\"\\n```\\n\\n**Key file paths:**\\n- \r\n`C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\docs\\\\cli\\\\agent.md`\\n- \r\n`C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\docs\\\\cli\\\\acp.md`\\n- \r\n`C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\docs\\\\cli\\\\sessions.md`\\n\\n### Summary\\n\\nThe \r\nprimary runtime invocation path is **`openclaw agent --agent <id> --message \\\"<text>\\\"`**. The `--local` flag bypasses \r\nthe Gateway for fully embedded execution. For code-level integration, the ACP bridge (`openclaw acp`) over stdio is \r\nthe intended mechanism. Sessions are storage/state constructs, not execution entry points themselves.\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\subagents\\runs.json:1205:      \"frozenResultText\": \"I now have enough to provide a \r\ncomprehensive, evidence-based answer. Here's what I found:\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Findings: OpenClaw Agent Execution, Sessions, \r\nand Python Runtime Integration\\n\\n### 1. `openclaw agents` - Agent Management (NOT execution)\\n\\n`openclaw agents` is \r\npurely a **configuration/management** command. It handles:\\n- `list`, `add`, `delete` - manage isolated agent \r\nidentities\\n- `bind/unbind` - route inbound channel traffic to agents\\n- `set-identity` - set name, avatar, \r\ntheme\\n\\n**It does NOT execute agents or run inference turns.** No `run`, `exec`, or `invoke` subcommand \r\nexists.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 2. `openclaw agent` - Single Turn Execution (via Gateway)\\n\\nThis is the concrete command for \r\nrunning one agent turn from scripts:\\n\\n```bash\\nopenclaw agent --agent ops --message \\\"Summarize logs\\\"\\nopenclaw \r\nagent --to +15555550123 --message \\\"status update\\\" --deliver\\nopenclaw agent --session-id 1234 --message \\\"Summarize \r\ninbox\\\" --thinking medium\\n```\\n\\n**Key behavior:**\\n- Routes through a running **Gateway** (WebSocket)\\n- `--local` \r\nflag for embedded mode (no Gateway)\\n- `--deliver` to route reply to a target channel\\n- Supports `--thinking`, \r\n`--model`, `--session-id`\\n\\n**This is the primary CLI hook for external integrations (including Python \r\nscripts).**\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 3. `sessions_spawn` Tool - Programmatic Sub-Agent Spawning\\n\\nFor agent-to-agent delegation \r\n(from within an agent turn, via tool calls):\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"tool\\\": \\\"sessions_spawn\\\",\\n  \\\"params\\\": {\\n    \r\n\\\"task\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n    \\\"runtime\\\": \\\"subagent\\\",  // or \\\"acp\\\"\\n    \\\"model\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n    \\\"label\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n  \r\n  \\\"runTimeoutSeconds\\\": 120\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n- `runtime: \\\"subagent\\\"`  spawns an OpenClaw sub-agent\\n- `runtime: \r\n\\\"acp\\\"`  spawns an ACP harness agent (IDE integrations)\\n- Sub-agents run in isolated sessions, can receive file \r\nattachments via `attachments[]`\\n- Controlled by `agents.list[].subagents.allowAgents`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 4. `openclaw acp` \r\n- ACP Bridge (for IDE/Python ACP harness)\\n\\nFor Python runtimes that speak the **Agent Client Protocol (ACP)** over \r\nstdio:\\n\\n```bash\\nopenclaw acp\\nopenclaw acp --url wss://gateway-host:18789 --token <token>\\nopenclaw acp --session \r\nagent:main:main\\n```\\n\\n- Bridges ACP stdio  Gateway WebSocket\\n- Keeps session state mapped to Gateway session \r\nkeys\\n- Supports `initialize`, `newSession`, `prompt`, `cancel`, `listSessions`\\n- Python process can act as ACP \r\nclient, spawning `openclaw acp` as a subprocess\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 5. `openclaw system event` - Inject System \r\nMessages\\n\\nFor triggering agent turns via system events (useful for automated workflows):\\n\\n```bash\\nopenclaw system \r\nevent --text \\\"Process new batch\\\" --mode now\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Practical Integration Pattern for Python \r\nRuntime\\n\\n**Option A - Direct turn trigger (simplest):**\\n```python\\nimport subprocess\\nresult = subprocess.run([\\n   \r\n \\\"openclaw\\\", \\\"agent\\\",\\n    \\\"--agent\\\", \\\"main\\\",\\n    \\\"--message\\\", \\\"Process video batch 42\\\",\\n    \r\n\\\"--deliver\\\"\\n], capture_output=True, text=True)\\n```\\n\\n**Option B - ACP protocol (fullest control):**\\n- Spawn \r\n`openclaw acp` as a subprocess\\n- Python runtime speaks ACP over stdio\\n- Supports session management, streaming, tool \r\nfollow-along\\n- Use `sessions_spawn` with `runtime: \\\"acp\\\"` from within agent turns to invoke Python ACP \r\nharnesses\\n\\n**Option C - Gateway WebSocket directly:**\\n- Connect to `ws://localhost:18789` (default Gateway port)\\n- \r\nUse `chat.send` or `agent` messages to drive turns programmatically\\n- Subscribe to `sessions.messages.subscribe` for \r\nstreaming results\\n\\n**Option D - `openclaw system event`:**\\n- Fire-and-forget injection into running agent \r\nsession\\n- Good for lightweight external triggers\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Summary\\n\\nThere is **no standalone `openclaw run` or \r\n`openclaw exec`** for agents. Runtime invocation is expected via:\\n1. **`openclaw agent`** - script-friendly CLI \r\nsingle-turn executor\\n2. **`sessions_spawn`** tool (inside agent turns) - for sub-agent delegation\\n3. **`openclaw \r\nacp`** - for Python/IDE ACP harness integration over stdio\\n4. **Gateway WebSocket API** - for full programmatic \r\ncontrol\\n5. **`openclaw system event`** - for injecting system prompts into running sessions\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\runtime_realcheck\\run_008\\b2\\sectors\\s3_visual_planning\\ch\r\neckpoints\\s3_final_checkpoint.json:6:  \"primitive\": \"exec + openclaw agent --agent ... --json\"\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\runtime_realcheck\\run_cli_probe\\b2\\sectors\\s3_visual_plann\r\ning\\checkpoints\\s3_final_checkpoint.json:6:  \"primitive\": \"exec + openclaw agent --agent ... --json\""}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1472,"aggregated":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\subagents\\runs.json:1139:      \"frozenResultText\": \"Here are the findings:\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \r\nResearch Findings: OpenClaw Agent Runtime Invocation\\n\\n### (1) Current CLI command to run an agent directly\\n\\n**Yes \r\n- `openclaw agent` exists today and is fully functional.**\\n\\n```bash\\n# Send a message to the main agent (via \r\nGateway)\\nopenclaw agent --agent main --message \\\"do something\\\"\\n\\n# Run embedded locally (requires API keys in shell \r\nenv - no Gateway needed)\\nopenclaw agent --agent main --message \\\"do something\\\" --local\\n\\n# Target a specific \r\nsession\\nopenclaw agent --session-id <id> --message \\\"text\\\"\\n\\n# Deliver reply back to a channel\\nopenclaw agent \r\n--agent ops --message \\\"Generate report\\\" --deliver --reply-channel slack --reply-to \\\"#reports\\\"\\n```\\n\\nSource: \r\n`docs/cli/agent.md` and `openclaw agent --help`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### (2) Two runtime paths exist\\n\\n| Mode | How | When \r\n|\\n|---|---|---|\\n| **Gateway-backed** (default) | Forwards to the running Gateway over WebSocket | Gateway must be \r\nrunning; normal operation |\\n| **Embedded/local** (`--local`) | Runs agent in-process directly | Requires provider API \r\nkeys in shell env; no Gateway needed |\\n\\n---\\n\\n### (3) Sessions/subagents/APIs are the standard bridge\\n\\nYes. The \r\nintended pattern for spawning isolated agent turns programmatically is:\\n\\n- **`openclaw agent`** - CLI one-shot \r\nturn\\n- **`openclaw acp`** - ACP protocol bridge over stdio for IDE integrations (forwards to Gateway via \r\nWebSocket)\\n- **Sessions** (`openclaw sessions`) - manage stored conversation state; not themselves an execution \r\nsurface\\n- **Cron jobs** (`openclaw cron`) - scheduled recurring agent turns\\n- **Hooks** - event-triggered agent \r\nturns\\n\\nThe ACP bridge (`openclaw acp`) is the intended path for programmatic IDE/code-level integration, and it \r\nroutes through the Gateway session system.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### (4) Concrete supported patterns today\\n\\n```bash\\n# One-shot \r\nagent turn (Gateway mode)\\nopenclaw agent --agent main --message \\\"Summarize logs\\\"\\n\\n# One-shot agent turn \r\n(embedded, no Gateway needed)\\nopenclaw agent --agent main --message \\\"Summarize logs\\\" --local\\n\\n# ACP bridge (for \r\nIDE integrations - speaks ACP over stdio, forwards to Gateway)\\nopenclaw acp\\nopenclaw acp --session \r\nagent:main:main\\nopenclaw acp --url wss://gateway-host:18789 --token <token>\\n\\n# Scheduled agent turn via \r\ncron\\nopenclaw cron add --job \\\"daily-report\\\" --schedule \\\"0 9 * * *\\\" --agent main --message \\\"Generate daily \r\nreport\\\"\\n\\n# Send message to channel (not agent turn, but triggers agent via channel routing)\\nopenclaw message send \r\n--channel telegram --target @user --message \\\"...\\\"\\n```\\n\\n**Key file paths:**\\n- \r\n`C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\docs\\\\cli\\\\agent.md`\\n- \r\n`C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\docs\\\\cli\\\\acp.md`\\n- \r\n`C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\docs\\\\cli\\\\sessions.md`\\n\\n### Summary\\n\\nThe \r\nprimary runtime invocation path is **`openclaw agent --agent <id> --message \\\"<text>\\\"`**. The `--local` flag bypasses \r\nthe Gateway for fully embedded execution. For code-level integration, the ACP bridge (`openclaw acp`) over stdio is \r\nthe intended mechanism. Sessions are storage/state constructs, not execution entry points themselves.\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\subagents\\runs.json:1205:      \"frozenResultText\": \"I now have enough to provide a \r\ncomprehensive, evidence-based answer. Here's what I found:\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Findings: OpenClaw Agent Execution, Sessions, \r\nand Python Runtime Integration\\n\\n### 1. `openclaw agents` - Agent Management (NOT execution)\\n\\n`openclaw agents` is \r\npurely a **configuration/management** command. It handles:\\n- `list`, `add`, `delete` - manage isolated agent \r\nidentities\\n- `bind/unbind` - route inbound channel traffic to agents\\n- `set-identity` - set name, avatar, \r\ntheme\\n\\n**It does NOT execute agents or run inference turns.** No `run`, `exec`, or `invoke` subcommand \r\nexists.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 2. `openclaw agent` - Single Turn Execution (via Gateway)\\n\\nThis is the concrete command for \r\nrunning one agent turn from scripts:\\n\\n```bash\\nopenclaw agent --agent ops --message \\\"Summarize logs\\\"\\nopenclaw \r\nagent --to +15555550123 --message \\\"status update\\\" --deliver\\nopenclaw agent --session-id 1234 --message \\\"Summarize \r\ninbox\\\" --thinking medium\\n```\\n\\n**Key behavior:**\\n- Routes through a running **Gateway** (WebSocket)\\n- `--local` \r\nflag for embedded mode (no Gateway)\\n- `--deliver` to route reply to a target channel\\n- Supports `--thinking`, \r\n`--model`, `--session-id`\\n\\n**This is the primary CLI hook for external integrations (including Python \r\nscripts).**\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 3. `sessions_spawn` Tool - Programmatic Sub-Agent Spawning\\n\\nFor agent-to-agent delegation \r\n(from within an agent turn, via tool calls):\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"tool\\\": \\\"sessions_spawn\\\",\\n  \\\"params\\\": {\\n    \r\n\\\"task\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n    \\\"runtime\\\": \\\"subagent\\\",  // or \\\"acp\\\"\\n    \\\"model\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n    \\\"label\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n  \r\n  \\\"runTimeoutSeconds\\\": 120\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n- `runtime: \\\"subagent\\\"`  spawns an OpenClaw sub-agent\\n- `runtime: \r\n\\\"acp\\\"`  spawns an ACP harness agent (IDE integrations)\\n- Sub-agents run in isolated sessions, can receive file \r\nattachments via `attachments[]`\\n- Controlled by `agents.list[].subagents.allowAgents`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 4. `openclaw acp` \r\n- ACP Bridge (for IDE/Python ACP harness)\\n\\nFor Python runtimes that speak the **Agent Client Protocol (ACP)** over \r\nstdio:\\n\\n```bash\\nopenclaw acp\\nopenclaw acp --url wss://gateway-host:18789 --token <token>\\nopenclaw acp --session \r\nagent:main:main\\n```\\n\\n- Bridges ACP stdio  Gateway WebSocket\\n- Keeps session state mapped to Gateway session \r\nkeys\\n- Supports `initialize`, `newSession`, `prompt`, `cancel`, `listSessions`\\n- Python process can act as ACP \r\nclient, spawning `openclaw acp` as a subprocess\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 5. `openclaw system event` - Inject System \r\nMessages\\n\\nFor triggering agent turns via system events (useful for automated workflows):\\n\\n```bash\\nopenclaw system \r\nevent --text \\\"Process new batch\\\" --mode now\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Practical Integration Pattern for Python \r\nRuntime\\n\\n**Option A - Direct turn trigger (simplest):**\\n```python\\nimport subprocess\\nresult = subprocess.run([\\n   \r\n \\\"openclaw\\\", \\\"agent\\\",\\n    \\\"--agent\\\", \\\"main\\\",\\n    \\\"--message\\\", \\\"Process video batch 42\\\",\\n    \r\n\\\"--deliver\\\"\\n], capture_output=True, text=True)\\n```\\n\\n**Option B - ACP protocol (fullest control):**\\n- Spawn \r\n`openclaw acp` as a subprocess\\n- Python runtime speaks ACP over stdio\\n- Supports session management, streaming, tool \r\nfollow-along\\n- Use `sessions_spawn` with `runtime: \\\"acp\\\"` from within agent turns to invoke Python ACP \r\nharnesses\\n\\n**Option C - Gateway WebSocket directly:**\\n- Connect to `ws://localhost:18789` (default Gateway port)\\n- \r\nUse `chat.send` or `agent` messages to drive turns programmatically\\n- Subscribe to `sessions.messages.subscribe` for \r\nstreaming results\\n\\n**Option D - `openclaw system event`:**\\n- Fire-and-forget injection into running agent \r\nsession\\n- Good for lightweight external triggers\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Summary\\n\\nThere is **no standalone `openclaw run` or \r\n`openclaw exec`** for agents. Runtime invocation is expected via:\\n1. **`openclaw agent`** - script-friendly CLI \r\nsingle-turn executor\\n2. **`sessions_spawn`** tool (inside agent turns) - for sub-agent delegation\\n3. **`openclaw \r\nacp`** - for Python/IDE ACP harness integration over stdio\\n4. **Gateway WebSocket API** - for full programmatic \r\ncontrol\\n5. **`openclaw system event`** - for injecting system prompts into running sessions\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\runtime_realcheck\\run_008\\b2\\sectors\\s3_visual_planning\\ch\r\neckpoints\\s3_final_checkpoint.json:6:  \"primitive\": \"exec + openclaw agent --agent ... --json\"\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\runtime_realcheck\\run_cli_probe\\b2\\sectors\\s3_visual_plann\r\ning\\checkpoints\\s3_final_checkpoint.json:6:  \"primitive\": \"exec + openclaw agent --agent ... --json\"","cwd":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s3_visual_planning"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775251341005}}
